  "texts": [
    "First, the number of access points to the network have multiplied.Each access point provides a cyber risk that needs to be managed.",
    "Second, many servers are connected, and new risks may come from this connectivity.",
    "\", p.191 11 Zetzsche, Arner [2] Lack of local support \"If a tech operation providing material financial infrastructure experiences difficulties, it is much more difficult to organize meaningful support for a decentralized network than for a concentrated system, where technical or financial support for one entity will mean that the entity providing the infrastructure has the technical or financial means to address the operational difficulties until a long-term solution can be worked out.",
    "\", p.191 Regulatory uncertainty From a legal perspective, DeFi may arguably undermine the rule of law, at least as we normally think about this from the standpoint of the Westphalian nation-state, and may also bring tech risks previously unknown and on a scale never before seen.",
    "\", p.184 12 Zook and Grote [124] Regulatory uncertainty \"The resulting cracks opened up voids of yet to be regulated space in which entrepreneurs eagerly sought profit and tried to provide proof of concept that the dream of decentralized finance was achievable."
  ]
}